WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.000
সাইট খুঁজে না পেলে ব্রাউজারে লিখুন:
-=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

00:17.480 --> 00:18.840
Excuse me, sir.

00:19.440 --> 00:20.840
Please come.

00:21.480 --> 00:22.560
The judge is here.

00:26.160 --> 00:27.160
CR CASE NO 673/2021

00:39.080 --> 00:41.760
[Tyagi] After viewing the evidence
and facts related to this case,

00:41.840 --> 00:43.560
the court has arrived at a verdict.

00:44.160 --> 00:45.240
Deepak Ahlawadi

00:47.160 --> 00:48.080
is guilty.

00:49.480 --> 00:54.120
In accordance
with IPC Sections 302 and 364,

00:55.400 --> 00:57.200
the verdict will be announced
to the defendant.

00:59.440 --> 01:03.840
In view of the gravity and seriousness
of this crime,

01:03.920 --> 01:07.200
the prosecution appeals to the court that
this case

01:07.280 --> 01:11.080
be treated as the rarest of rare cases,
milord.

01:11.680 --> 01:13.840
And therefore Deepak Ahlawadi…

01:16.000 --> 01:17.320
be given the death sentence.

01:17.400 --> 01:19.120
[people murmuring]

01:24.320 --> 01:25.320
[parent sobbing]

01:32.440 --> 01:35.480
[lawyer] Your Honour,
Deepak is only 24 years old.

01:35.560 --> 01:36.960
He has his whole life ahead of him--

01:37.040 --> 01:38.800
[parent 2] And what about
the lives of my sons?

01:40.000 --> 01:41.600
They were even younger than him.

01:46.360 --> 01:50.440
The defense makes an appeal that
the culprit be granted a life sentence.

02:04.800 --> 02:06.560
The court will take a short recess.

02:10.400 --> 02:12.280
The verdict will be announced
this evening.

02:13.000 --> 02:13.960
Adjourned.

02:17.840 --> 02:19.480
- [Order] Looking good, sir.
- [Mintu] Turban is fine?

02:19.560 --> 02:21.120
- Yeah, fine.
- Now spray me.

02:21.840 --> 02:23.400
I wanna smell good.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.200
Some more this side, spray me all over,
the back too.

02:26.280 --> 02:27.480
Go for it, go for it.

02:28.160 --> 02:29.200
But, Mintu bro?

02:29.280 --> 02:31.160
- Yeah.
- How you gonna recognise Binu?

02:31.680 --> 02:32.880
- I'll tell you what.
- Hmm.

02:33.400 --> 02:34.360
Shut your eyes.

02:37.400 --> 02:38.400
Done.

02:38.480 --> 02:41.560
Now imagine the cutest girl in the world.

02:42.480 --> 02:43.480
Go on.

02:46.520 --> 02:47.800
- Can you see her?
- [sighs] I see her.

02:48.680 --> 02:50.960
Oh, I am on cloud 9.

02:55.440 --> 02:57.480
- But why would the world's cutest girl…
- Yeah?

02:57.560 --> 02:58.520
…want to hang out with you?

03:00.080 --> 03:01.280
Maybe not the cutest.

03:01.880 --> 03:03.320
Why not?

03:03.400 --> 03:04.400
Meet her and find out.

03:04.480 --> 03:06.440
She could be the cutest girl in the world.

03:06.520 --> 03:07.440
That's true.

03:07.520 --> 03:08.800
[Munshi] So,

03:08.880 --> 03:10.920
decided on a name for the chamber?

03:11.000 --> 03:12.640
Mr Munshi, it's best if you decide.

03:13.240 --> 03:15.480
We don't want to argue over it anymore.

03:15.560 --> 03:16.560
Why not?

03:17.080 --> 03:18.840
You are both partners now, aren't you?

03:19.440 --> 03:21.640
But that's exactly why
we want you to decide,

03:21.720 --> 03:24.920
whether it's Balli Negi & Associates
or Negi Balli & Associates.

03:25.000 --> 03:26.480
Could you decide by this evening
and let us know?

03:26.560 --> 03:27.440
[Munshi chuckles]

03:27.520 --> 03:29.680
Just don't forget that
I am like a daughter to you.

03:29.760 --> 03:31.160
- [chuckling continues]
- Sorry.

03:33.120 --> 03:34.280
All right then, Mr Munshi.

03:34.360 --> 03:36.400
I have a very important meeting to attend.

03:36.480 --> 03:38.320
- All the best.
- See you later. Thank you, sir.

03:40.400 --> 03:42.360
[Order] The cutest girl in the world!

03:45.440 --> 03:47.040
Mr Munshi, I too have a meeting.

03:47.120 --> 03:48.360
I am so cute. [giggles]

03:48.440 --> 03:49.720
[Munshi] Okay.

03:55.280 --> 03:58.280
[Ani whispering] Mr Banaspati,
please hide your armpits.

04:00.280 --> 04:02.600
[groans]

04:03.480 --> 04:07.160
Madam, who is this person
you're asking me to hide my armpits for?

04:07.680 --> 04:10.480
[Ani] This is the in-house counsel
for Fire Clone Deodorant.

04:11.080 --> 04:12.720
Venkat Balakrishnan.

04:12.800 --> 04:15.360
He gets a very detailed account
of all inspection.

04:15.440 --> 04:16.720
- [Vishwas] Ani.
- [Ani] Hmm?

04:16.800 --> 04:19.640
He is on the job, our Shambhu Sherlock.

04:20.800 --> 04:23.720
Are you sure this is gonna work?
I need to know what they're up to.

04:24.320 --> 04:26.800
Ani, they say
monkeys have an excellent memory.

04:26.880 --> 04:31.240
So if you want to know what's going on,
you better keep your ears to the ground.

04:40.040 --> 04:42.040
[Nayana] Why are you settling, Mr Venkat?

04:42.120 --> 04:43.640
We are clearly winning.

04:43.720 --> 04:44.960
Are we?

04:45.040 --> 04:48.120
Ananya has issued an inspection order
for the manufacturing plant.

04:48.640 --> 04:50.280
It's not like we are hiding something.

04:51.240 --> 04:52.240
[Nayana] Of course, sir.

04:53.120 --> 04:54.360
I give you my word.

04:54.440 --> 04:55.440
[Shambhu] Uh…

04:56.080 --> 04:57.640
Give word.

04:58.240 --> 04:59.600
Inspection never happened.

04:59.680 --> 05:03.440
Okay. But there has been some recent
development which you should know about.

05:06.720 --> 05:09.160
What happened to your excellent memory?
Can't your remember?

05:10.000 --> 05:11.280
It's a buy-out.

05:11.360 --> 05:12.440
Buy-out?

05:12.960 --> 05:13.960
Bite.

05:15.000 --> 05:16.000
Bite?

05:17.800 --> 05:19.720
Now what could "bite" mean
in the middle of all this?

05:19.800 --> 05:21.160
[Shambhu] What I heard
is what I'm telling you.

05:21.240 --> 05:24.440
Don't ask me what it means. They are
big shots. They say what they like.

05:24.520 --> 05:28.280
[chuckles] As she was leaving,
Nayana referred to Ani as a cat.

05:28.360 --> 05:29.360
A cat?

05:29.440 --> 05:34.000
Yeah. She said, she is a pussy.
A cat and pussy are the same thing, right?

05:34.080 --> 05:35.920
How dare she call me a cat!

05:36.640 --> 05:39.840
She is a cat. Her father is a cat.
Even her dog is a cat.

05:39.920 --> 05:40.880
[Shambhu] Mm-hmm.

05:40.960 --> 05:42.960
I'll make sure
the inspection happens today.

05:45.720 --> 05:46.720
Binu,

05:47.400 --> 05:48.440
I love you.

05:52.240 --> 05:53.720
- Mintu.
- Yes.

05:55.200 --> 05:56.240
You are an idiot.

05:56.320 --> 05:58.400
- [tires screeching]
- [car horns honking]

05:58.480 --> 06:00.760
No, I mean that's what Binu will say.

06:00.840 --> 06:01.840
Why?

06:01.920 --> 06:03.840
Dude, who says
"I love you" on the first date?

06:03.920 --> 06:05.040
You daft or something?

06:05.120 --> 06:07.080
First you talk to each other,
work up a rapport.

06:07.160 --> 06:09.160
Then say "I love you". "I love you."

06:09.240 --> 06:11.560
But we have already chatted so much
all through the night.

06:11.640 --> 06:13.400
Once we get married we'll find out.

06:14.960 --> 06:16.400
Bro, you're planning to talk marriage too?

06:16.480 --> 06:17.760
Of course.

06:17.840 --> 06:20.080
Hey, I am sorry, Mintu.
I mean I am really sorry.

06:20.160 --> 06:22.040
I had no idea you were so serious.

06:22.120 --> 06:23.040
Shall we try again?

06:24.840 --> 06:26.360
- Let's do a better one.
- All right.

06:26.440 --> 06:28.080
We'll do a better one, okay?

06:28.800 --> 06:29.800
Binu,

06:30.600 --> 06:32.160
will you marry me?

06:32.240 --> 06:33.240
Mintu.

06:33.320 --> 06:34.320
Yes?

06:34.960 --> 06:37.200
- You are an absolute idiot.
- Binu would never say that.

06:37.280 --> 06:38.800
No, no. Actually that's what I am saying.

06:39.440 --> 06:40.560
Piss off!

06:41.120 --> 06:42.280
Go and wait downstairs.

06:43.040 --> 06:45.680
Screwed up my whole bloody mood, idiot,
talking such bullshit.

06:45.760 --> 06:49.120
Fine. I'll go and wait downstairs.
That's just what Binu is gonna say.

06:50.360 --> 06:53.560
[Ani] There's only one way we can
win this case for Banaspati, Vishwas.

06:53.640 --> 06:55.680
[Vishwas] Now what options
do we have left?

06:59.640 --> 07:01.160
Ani, where have you brought me to?

07:01.760 --> 07:03.760
Well Tricks Manufacturing and Packaging.

07:03.840 --> 07:06.600
They are the contract manufacturers
for Fire Clone.

07:06.680 --> 07:09.400
Yes, that's all very well.
But what's the plan?

07:10.800 --> 07:14.120
Vishwas,
when all the options are exhausted,

07:14.680 --> 07:15.840
what do journalists do?

07:15.920 --> 07:17.040
They become sell-outs.

07:18.640 --> 07:21.720
The ones that don't sell out,
what do they do?

07:21.800 --> 07:22.880
They end up in jail.

07:22.960 --> 07:24.920
Sting, Vishwas.

07:25.800 --> 07:26.800
Sting.

07:27.520 --> 07:28.640
Sting.

07:30.480 --> 07:32.120
- A pen with a hidden camera?
- Mm-hmm.

07:33.080 --> 07:35.560
We're going on behalf
of Dalival Consumer Products.

07:36.360 --> 07:37.360
[clears throat]

07:39.880 --> 07:42.600
Hi. I am Falguni Dalival.

07:42.680 --> 07:44.760
NRI. Founder.

07:47.320 --> 07:48.640
Hi.

07:48.720 --> 07:52.520
I am Balvindar Pratap Singh Oberoi.
Co-founder.

07:57.000 --> 07:59.680
Hi. I am Balvindar Pratap.
Regional Manager.

08:04.440 --> 08:07.200
I'm liaison agent, Ballu. Okay?

08:08.520 --> 08:09.520
Ballu.

08:10.240 --> 08:11.080
Ballu.

08:12.800 --> 08:13.880
Hang on a minute.

08:14.440 --> 08:15.640
What if we get caught?

08:16.360 --> 08:19.200
We need like a code or something,
some… some kind of secret signal.

08:19.880 --> 08:20.720
[sucks teeth]

08:20.800 --> 08:23.040
Hmm. Nice. Nice.

08:23.120 --> 08:25.720
[sucks teeth] We'll do it twice.
[sucks teeth]

08:25.800 --> 08:27.080
This is nice.

08:27.160 --> 08:31.920
Your Honour, take a look at this.
The State of Orissa vs Mukesh Bhan.

08:32.000 --> 08:36.320
This case was the first time the offender
was given the death sentence,

08:36.400 --> 08:37.480
as per section 302.

08:37.560 --> 08:41.000
Your Honour, that crime was
far more brutal compared to this.

08:41.080 --> 08:43.360
In that case,
both kids were under the age of 13.

08:43.440 --> 08:46.600
And in this case, one kid was 16.
So we pardon him?

08:46.680 --> 08:48.840
Mr PP you know quite well what I meant.

08:49.760 --> 08:51.600
But that's just how the law perceives it.

08:51.680 --> 08:52.840
[scoffs]

08:52.920 --> 08:56.880
The law also perceives that
the crime was pre-meditated.

08:56.960 --> 08:59.200
Deepak planned everything
before he went there.

09:00.320 --> 09:02.840
Sir, by virtue
of being a Public Prosecutor,

09:03.360 --> 09:06.000
it is my duty
to appeal for the death sentence.

09:08.200 --> 09:10.360
But in this case,
by virtue of being a common citizen,

09:10.440 --> 09:12.080
I make the same appeal.

09:13.600 --> 09:15.160
Whatever Deepak has done,

09:16.120 --> 09:17.840
society will never forgive him for it.

09:18.960 --> 09:19.960
Never.

09:25.560 --> 09:26.560
Ah…

09:28.040 --> 09:31.120
You leave the files here with me,
I'll take a look.

09:31.200 --> 09:33.280
- Yes, Your Honour. Sure.
- Yes, Your Honour.

09:42.440 --> 09:43.440
Mintu.

09:44.840 --> 09:46.280
Mintu, I'm sorry.

09:46.360 --> 09:47.360
Uh…

09:47.880 --> 09:49.160
I'm Binu.

09:55.400 --> 09:57.080
Hey. Sujata, you here?

09:57.160 --> 09:58.320
[chuckles]

09:58.400 --> 09:59.400
How come?

09:59.480 --> 10:01.360
I love this place.

10:02.280 --> 10:03.600
Uh… Uh…

10:03.680 --> 10:04.680
[person] Hi!

10:11.400 --> 10:13.360
- How are you?
- [person 2] Good. How are you?

10:13.440 --> 10:14.280
I am good.

10:14.360 --> 10:15.600
Uh… Sorry. Uh…

10:16.480 --> 10:18.160
- Hi!
- I, uh…

10:18.960 --> 10:20.480
I'm waiting for Binu actually.

10:20.560 --> 10:21.560
[Mintu] Mm-hmm.

10:22.400 --> 10:24.400
- You're all dolled up today.
- [chuckles]

10:25.280 --> 10:27.160
- You have an important client meeting?
- Yeah.

10:27.840 --> 10:29.160
But, uh…

10:29.920 --> 10:31.640
I just got a message from him.

10:31.720 --> 10:35.960
He's tied up somewhere. So,
I'll see you back at the chamber later?

10:37.760 --> 10:38.720
Uh… Sujata, listen.

10:38.800 --> 10:39.880
Um…

10:39.960 --> 10:43.240
I had told Binu that when we meet,

10:43.320 --> 10:45.320
we'll exchange our favourite things
with each other.

10:47.800 --> 10:50.120
My favourite is this dessert. Um…

10:51.000 --> 10:52.200
Do you think she will find it weird?

10:52.280 --> 10:53.840
Uh… Why weird?

10:54.800 --> 10:57.360
The thing is Order was telling me

10:57.440 --> 11:00.280
you cant offer home made dessert
when you go on a date.

11:01.600 --> 11:04.720
But that dessert, you made it yourself?

11:04.800 --> 11:06.440
[chuckles]

11:06.520 --> 11:07.920
I am sure she'll love it.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.800
Your… Binu, I mean.

11:25.400 --> 11:29.040
Wow. Only two kinds of people give
an advance in the first meeting.

11:32.240 --> 11:33.440
They are either scammers

11:35.080 --> 11:36.360
or industrialists.

11:38.520 --> 11:39.520
And Ms Falguni,

11:39.600 --> 11:42.520
one look at you and I can tell
you're a daughter of an industrialist.

11:44.240 --> 11:45.360
So, shall we?

11:46.440 --> 11:47.320
What?

11:48.040 --> 11:49.840
Uh… I mean plant.

11:49.920 --> 11:51.160
- I'll show you the plant.
- Yeah.

11:51.240 --> 11:52.320
- [chuckling]
- Absolutely.

11:52.400 --> 11:53.400
- Shall we?
- That's cool.

11:53.480 --> 11:56.800
By the way, Ms Falguni,
are you a pure NRI?

11:56.880 --> 11:57.920
- Pure.
- I see.

11:58.520 --> 11:59.600
So was my ex.

12:00.240 --> 12:02.800
By the way, before you understand
what your own requirements are,

12:02.880 --> 12:05.280
you need to understand the requirements
of the average Indian customer.

12:05.360 --> 12:06.360
Sure.

12:06.440 --> 12:08.680
Do you know what is the one thing
they require most?

12:08.760 --> 12:09.720
Price.

12:11.120 --> 12:12.360
Vishwas.

12:13.000 --> 12:15.120
[stammering] Ballu.

12:16.320 --> 12:18.120
Ballu? Vishwas.

12:18.200 --> 12:19.200
[stammers]

12:19.280 --> 12:21.760
Vishwas the hindi word for trust?

12:21.840 --> 12:23.880
Correct. Trust.

12:23.960 --> 12:25.800
And how do we gain people's trust?

12:25.880 --> 12:27.880
Um… By delivering quality products?

12:27.960 --> 12:29.720
No, no, no. Not quality products my dear.

12:29.800 --> 12:31.800
All failed businesses make this mistake.

12:31.880 --> 12:35.160
See, you don't need to deliver quality.
You just need to promise to deliver it.

12:35.240 --> 12:38.120
Trust is gained from packaging.
Dump anything at all in the product.

12:38.200 --> 12:39.600
Just make sure you package it well.

12:40.280 --> 12:43.480
[Ani] But that's
kind of like horrible advice.

12:44.000 --> 12:47.760
If you just put anything in it,
then why would customers buy it?

12:48.360 --> 12:51.560
- So cute, Ma'am. So cute.
- Thank you.

12:51.640 --> 12:52.640
Tell me one thing.

12:53.280 --> 12:54.680
Customers buy bread, right?

12:54.760 --> 12:55.760
Absolutely.

12:57.920 --> 12:58.920
Check this out.

12:59.480 --> 13:01.520
\Grains of wheat, A pretty smiling face.

13:01.600 --> 13:03.600
And "whole wheat bread" written
in big bold letters.

13:04.360 --> 13:05.760
That's it! You've won their trust.

13:05.840 --> 13:07.520
Who is gonna check what's actually in it?

13:07.600 --> 13:08.880
What is in it?

13:08.960 --> 13:09.880
Refined flour.

13:09.960 --> 13:12.200
- What?
- Brown wheat is just 25%.

13:12.280 --> 13:14.560
- And 25% doesn't make the grade.
- [chuckles]

13:14.640 --> 13:17.200
You mean everyday I am having
refined flour bread with my fruit jam?

13:17.280 --> 13:18.280
Jam!

13:18.960 --> 13:19.880
And fruits in the

13:21.000 --> 13:22.640
- packaging.
- Packaging!

13:22.720 --> 13:25.520
But isn't this illegal? We can't
be lying to our customers like this.

13:25.600 --> 13:26.760
But who says we're lying?

13:27.800 --> 13:28.800
Everything is mentioned

13:29.840 --> 13:31.040
on the label here.

13:34.000 --> 13:35.120
Oh, God. I've never read this.

13:35.200 --> 13:37.360
- No one bothers, sir. No one reads it.
- [mumbles]

13:37.440 --> 13:39.680
The word customer itself has the word
"cursed" in it.

13:39.760 --> 13:43.040
They only read the MRP
and expiry date, isn't it?

13:43.120 --> 13:45.040
And you don't tamper with those I hope.

13:45.120 --> 13:46.800
No, no. That's completely illegal.

13:46.880 --> 13:49.320
We have some principles.
Principles cost more.

13:50.120 --> 13:51.400
They're expensive.

13:51.480 --> 13:53.120
Come this way.
I'll show you what else we've got.

13:53.200 --> 13:54.560
They're cheating us.

13:54.640 --> 13:57.000
Vishwas, can you please leave the jam?
Get over it.

13:57.080 --> 13:58.440
- Come!
- How can you…

13:58.520 --> 13:59.960
In character, please.

14:00.040 --> 14:03.440
\Come, come. These are all
expired products being loaded.

14:03.520 --> 14:04.520
\Please.

14:04.600 --> 14:06.160
\- Come on, guys. Buck up, buck up. Move it.
- [mouthing]

14:06.760 --> 14:08.600
\- Come on guys, hurry up.
- [Ani clears throat]

14:08.680 --> 14:11.120
\Faster, faster. Yes, move it. Good job.

14:14.760 --> 14:17.200
\[sucking teeth]

14:19.080 --> 14:20.480
\[sucking continues]

14:28.080 --> 14:29.040
\Excuse me?

14:29.840 --> 14:31.320
\Sorry I thought you were… [chuckles]

14:31.400 --> 14:32.800
\…what I was trying to say was

14:32.880 --> 14:35.960
\all Fire Clone's expired goods
are sold by us.

14:36.040 --> 14:37.040
\[Ani] Oh!

14:38.160 --> 14:40.560
\Madam, in the market,

14:40.640 --> 14:44.600
\the very best low quality products,
only people like us will buy.

14:44.680 --> 14:46.600
\- Yeah, that's pretty obvious. Of course.
- [chuckles]

14:46.680 --> 14:50.400
\- That's what we wanted to hear, Mr Rajesh.
- Thank you. Thank you. Any time.

14:50.480 --> 14:51.920
\- [Ani] Uh… Ballu.
- Hmm?

14:52.000 --> 14:53.440
\- Send him a request for quotation.
- Of course, Ma'am.

14:53.520 --> 14:54.840
\- Thank you.
- Hey. But wait.

14:54.920 --> 14:56.120
\At least take my card, ma'am.

14:56.840 --> 14:59.240
\- Lovely! Thank you so much.
- And may I have your number if you…

14:59.320 --> 15:02.160
\I left my phone at the office.
Can you give me a missed call?

15:02.240 --> 15:04.920
\[stammering] My phone is not working.
So it's fine.

15:05.000 --> 15:07.840
\No, no, no. Don't worry.
I'll write down my number for you. Uh…

15:07.920 --> 15:08.840
\Ballu, pen.

15:08.000 --> 15:18.000
Downloaded from -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

15:12.280 --> 15:14.080
\Ballu, pen.

15:14.680 --> 15:16.000
- [sucking teeth]
- Pen.

15:16.080 --> 15:17.560
Uh… [chuckles]

15:18.320 --> 15:19.440
Ballu.

15:21.000 --> 15:21.920
Ballu, the pen.

15:22.000 --> 15:23.800
- Hey, I'm just asking for your pen.
- No, no.

15:23.880 --> 15:25.200
Why are you acting so weird?

15:25.280 --> 15:26.680
Sir!

15:26.760 --> 15:28.520
Sir, that's not a pen, sir.

15:28.600 --> 15:30.360
Sir, I'm not a professional, sir.

15:30.960 --> 15:33.040
I've never carried out a sting operation
in my life.

15:33.120 --> 15:35.320
Sir, these guys won't beat me up, I hope.

15:35.400 --> 15:37.080
- Vishwas!
- Yes. Of course they will…

15:37.680 --> 15:39.000
- Vishwas.
- Why this?

15:39.600 --> 15:41.880
It's my first time, sir.
That's why I messed up.

15:41.960 --> 15:43.200
Vishwas, stop it.

15:43.280 --> 15:44.560
Ask him. Why is he… Ma'am.

15:45.440 --> 15:46.960
\TRUTH ALONE TRIUMPHS

15:47.040 --> 15:48.360
[Munshi] Your Honour.

15:49.040 --> 15:52.640
Our justice system believes
only in reform,

15:53.360 --> 15:54.720
not in punishment.

15:57.720 --> 15:59.880
In that case,
no one should get the death sentence.

16:01.720 --> 16:03.680
Everyone should get a chance at reform.

16:03.760 --> 16:04.760
Of course, they should.

16:05.880 --> 16:09.000
But the justice system also believes

16:09.080 --> 16:12.720
that sometimes,
in the rarest of rare cases,

16:13.360 --> 16:15.480
the possibility of change is impossible.

16:16.320 --> 16:19.000
The culprit is beyond reform.

16:20.080 --> 16:25.960
And it's in
society's best interest that he…

16:26.040 --> 16:27.880
[Topo] No, Mr Munshi.

16:29.160 --> 16:31.320
Who are we to decide who is beyond reform

16:31.400 --> 16:33.240
and should be given the death sentence?

16:35.320 --> 16:37.480
And what is beyond reform mean anyway?

16:38.800 --> 16:41.520
How can anyone decide that
so-and-so is beyond reform?

16:41.600 --> 16:43.120
He is never going to improve?

16:45.040 --> 16:47.920
I believe in a justice system that's
over and above ours.

16:48.840 --> 16:52.720
According to which, the right
to give or take a life lies only with Him.

16:53.320 --> 16:55.400
[fading] These decisions are not
for us to take.

16:55.920 --> 16:57.600
We are mere mortals, Your Honour.

16:58.920 --> 17:00.200
Eat something, Son.

17:00.280 --> 17:02.240
Try and eat something at least.

17:02.320 --> 17:03.320
[sniffles]

17:19.640 --> 17:21.520
I made a terrible mistake, Mom.

17:25.520 --> 17:27.240
[sobbing]

17:27.760 --> 17:30.560
I don't know what's going to
happen to me now.

17:37.280 --> 17:39.560
[officer] Does he have regrets
over what he has done?

17:39.640 --> 17:42.880
He cries sometimes.
But he is also very hot-tempered.

17:42.960 --> 17:44.840
He has sent three prisoners
to hospital already.

17:45.440 --> 17:46.760
And a guard too.

17:47.360 --> 17:50.320
Any diagnosis of mental disorder
during his counselling?

17:50.400 --> 17:53.120
Sir, the psychiatrist's report says
he is mentally stable.

17:55.720 --> 17:56.720
All right.

17:59.920 --> 18:00.920
Your Honour.

18:02.480 --> 18:04.920
I have been working as a prison guard
for 30 years.

18:06.440 --> 18:11.040
So far I haven't met anyone
who is completely bad.

18:12.880 --> 18:15.240
If you observe a criminal
when he is with his mother,

18:15.920 --> 18:17.520
he's as human as any of us.

18:18.800 --> 18:20.480
So if you are looking for
some kind of stamp

18:21.440 --> 18:23.280
or some kind of character certificate

18:24.480 --> 18:26.920
that can guarantee that
Deepak is beyond reform,

18:28.000 --> 18:29.400
I don't think you will find it.

18:36.160 --> 18:37.440
[Munshi] Your Honour.

18:37.520 --> 18:40.000
What you need now is not advice.

18:40.640 --> 18:42.320
What you need is someone to guide you.

18:43.400 --> 18:45.360
There is someone who comes to mind,

18:45.440 --> 18:46.800
who can do this for you.

18:54.160 --> 18:56.520
If you agree, I can talk to him.

18:59.160 --> 19:01.360
Please come to the hearing, Mr Venkat.

19:01.440 --> 19:03.480
I assure you we have something
worth celebrating, sir.

19:04.120 --> 19:05.920
Yes! I'll see you.

19:06.000 --> 19:07.000
[Vishwas] No, no, no.

19:07.560 --> 19:09.040
I cannot believe this.

19:09.760 --> 19:12.360
Am I very lucky or are you very dumb?

19:12.440 --> 19:16.080
Nayana, Fire Clone is
selling expired products.

19:17.440 --> 19:19.280
You can't hide the truth for much longer.

19:20.320 --> 19:24.120
- May the truth prevail.
- The truth may prevail, dear Ani.

19:24.760 --> 19:26.600
And in your case, it may never.

19:28.440 --> 19:32.640
Trespassing private property,
impersonation, recording without consent.

19:33.480 --> 19:35.520
If this goes to court,
you are going to be so…

19:35.600 --> 19:36.600
Go ahead.

19:38.240 --> 19:40.040
I'm not scared of losing my bar license.

19:40.120 --> 19:41.120
I know.

19:41.800 --> 19:43.840
- But what about Mr Court Manager here?
- I'm scared.

19:44.360 --> 19:45.640
- I'm scared.
- Really?

19:45.720 --> 19:47.560
- Mmm.
- Being a government servant,

19:47.640 --> 19:50.160
you carry out a sting operation
in a private case?

19:50.240 --> 19:52.200
- Ms Nayana.
- She's a bad influence on you.

19:52.280 --> 19:53.600
Ms Nayana, I know.

19:54.640 --> 19:56.160
My engagement just broke off.

19:56.240 --> 19:57.720
Of course, that can be fixed.

19:58.960 --> 20:01.520
But once you lose a government job,
that can never be fixed.

20:01.600 --> 20:03.720
So please can you forget it?

20:04.640 --> 20:07.160
- Keep him out of this, I'm warning you.
- Yes, keep me out of this.

20:07.240 --> 20:09.360
Well, that depends on you.

20:10.040 --> 20:13.040
You will have to admit defeat
in front of everyone in court.

20:13.120 --> 20:16.560
And you will have to testify that
you took on this case only for money

20:16.640 --> 20:17.640
and publicity.

20:23.440 --> 20:24.440
Please.

20:26.480 --> 20:27.480
Fine.

20:27.560 --> 20:28.560
Fine.

20:29.200 --> 20:30.800
And you, come with me.

20:31.320 --> 20:33.440
Sorry, Ma'am.
I was just trying to explain that…

20:33.520 --> 20:34.640
I couldn't stop myself.

20:34.720 --> 20:36.960
But I was the one who caught them.
I discovered the pen.

20:37.040 --> 20:39.400
Fire Clone should hear
nothing about all this.

20:39.480 --> 20:41.800
- Why?
- Because there's been a development.

20:43.240 --> 20:44.640
Not a soul should hear.

20:47.440 --> 20:49.040
[phone buzzes]

20:50.560 --> 20:52.280
[Law] Mintu sir is not taking my calls.
Get him to call me.

20:52.960 --> 20:54.280
- I can't do it, man.
- Look, Order.

20:54.360 --> 20:57.200
This file has to get to the High Court.
Please get him to call me. It's urgent.

20:57.280 --> 20:58.680
I just told you I can't do it.

20:58.760 --> 21:00.080
He's in a shit mood.

21:02.760 --> 21:03.760
Looks like he's even crying.

21:04.600 --> 21:07.120
- He's crying?
- He's mixed up with that bloody chick.

21:07.200 --> 21:09.240
They were chatting online.
She didn't show up on their date.

21:10.040 --> 21:11.040
What chick?

21:11.120 --> 21:12.920
Listen, I can't tell you anything, bro.

21:13.000 --> 21:14.720
And how will it help
knowing her name is Binu Bindra?

21:18.440 --> 21:20.880
Mr Banaspati is losing
because of his lawyer.

21:20.960 --> 21:22.640
[Vishwas] No, Ani, that's not true at all.

21:24.120 --> 21:26.520
There's just one thing
I don't really understand.

21:27.040 --> 21:28.320
The recording is with Nayana.

21:29.480 --> 21:31.000
If you open your mouth,
you're gonna lose your job.

21:31.080 --> 21:32.800
I may have already lost my job.

21:32.880 --> 21:35.360
Then why isn't she telling the client
about the sting?

21:36.480 --> 21:37.600
Bite.

21:38.200 --> 21:39.080
Bite.

21:39.160 --> 21:42.160
Didn't he say something about a bite?
That's where the catch is.

21:42.240 --> 21:45.680
Hey, Shambhu. Why don't you try
and remember his exact words?

21:47.400 --> 21:48.480
Mmm…

21:50.520 --> 21:51.560
Bro.

21:52.800 --> 21:54.520
"Bi" was definitely in it.

21:55.560 --> 21:56.760
Bi…

21:56.840 --> 21:57.880
Biceps.

21:58.720 --> 21:59.840
Bi…

21:59.920 --> 22:01.560
- Bisexual!
- Nope.

22:02.720 --> 22:06.120
Sujata, you had told me once that
if I use tricks, I could win the case.

22:06.200 --> 22:07.200
- [Vishwas] Bison.
- [Shambhu] Uh-uh.

22:07.280 --> 22:09.520
I've tried everything, and here we are,
by guessing.

22:09.600 --> 22:11.240
[Vishwas] Bailababa. Bailamos.

22:11.880 --> 22:13.760
I too am caught
in a jam trying tricks, Ani.

22:13.840 --> 22:14.880
[Vishwas] Bye, dude.

22:15.720 --> 22:16.560
Why?

22:17.560 --> 22:18.560
What happened?

22:19.080 --> 22:20.400
[Vishwas] Bi… By-product.

22:20.480 --> 22:21.920
Bi… Bicycle.

22:22.000 --> 22:22.880
Mm-mmm.

22:22.960 --> 22:24.280
Bypass?

22:24.360 --> 22:27.000
- [Ani] Enough. Can you stop it, Vishwas?
- [Shambhu] No.

22:27.080 --> 22:28.800
We're out of options, okay?

22:28.880 --> 22:29.920
Yeah!

22:30.000 --> 22:31.520
It was something like that,

22:31.600 --> 22:32.840
what you said just now.

22:32.920 --> 22:35.720
We are out option. Out!

22:35.800 --> 22:37.400
- Be-out!
- Be-out?

22:38.240 --> 22:39.680
- Be-out!
- [Vishwas] Be-out…

22:40.200 --> 22:41.960
- Buy-out!
- Ah, yes.

22:42.040 --> 22:43.680
Buy-out! Buy-out! Buy-out!

22:43.760 --> 22:46.000
Fire Clone is being bought by someone.

22:46.600 --> 22:48.320
That's why the inspection was cancelled.

22:48.400 --> 22:51.680
If the expired products issue is leaked
in the market,

22:51.760 --> 22:53.360
then their deal will get screwed.

22:53.440 --> 22:54.720
Very true. Yeah, yeah.

22:54.800 --> 22:57.160
- That's why Venkat was panicking.
- Yes!

22:57.840 --> 22:59.360
Yeah…

22:59.440 --> 23:01.240
And Sujata, you've always said,

23:01.320 --> 23:03.320
"If the client's in a panic,
he won't even listen to his lawyer."

23:04.040 --> 23:05.960
That's why Nayana didn't mention
the sting operation to him…

23:06.040 --> 23:07.040
[chuckles]

23:07.120 --> 23:08.960
Because she's willing to do anything
to defeat Ani.

23:09.040 --> 23:10.040
Of course.

23:10.640 --> 23:13.160
You still have some tricks
up your sleeve, sister!

23:16.480 --> 23:19.040
- [Vishwas clears throat]
- Reason, reward, ragging are done.

23:19.120 --> 23:20.560
Rule. Divide and rule.

23:20.640 --> 23:23.720
Use it to split up Nayana and her client.

23:25.840 --> 23:26.840
Ballu.

23:27.520 --> 23:28.680
Get a notice ready.

23:31.560 --> 23:33.840
How dare you send us a legal notice,
Mr Venkat?

23:34.360 --> 23:36.440
You betray our principles
then slap a case against us?

23:36.520 --> 23:37.960
Case? What case?

23:38.560 --> 23:39.400
This way, sir.

23:39.480 --> 23:40.880
I see. You think I'm a fool.

23:40.960 --> 23:42.720
Don't try and sell me
your fake innocence, okay?

23:42.800 --> 23:44.920
Sir, you're betraying us
because of a sting operation?

23:45.000 --> 23:47.120
We trust you, and this is how you operate?

23:47.200 --> 23:48.560
Sting operation?

23:48.640 --> 23:50.920
Oh, come on. Cut the drama, sir.

23:51.000 --> 23:52.080
[line clicks]

23:53.800 --> 23:55.000
Let's go, sir.

23:56.280 --> 23:57.760
Was there a sting operation today?

23:59.040 --> 23:59.920
Who told you?

24:00.000 --> 24:01.160
Why didn't you tell me this?

24:01.240 --> 24:03.640
You're well aware
there's a buy-out negotiation on.

24:03.720 --> 24:04.720
This can't come out.

24:04.800 --> 24:06.320
It won't, sir. It won't.

24:06.400 --> 24:07.600
Nayana, now listen to me.

24:07.680 --> 24:11.720
We have to put an end to this case
right now. I can't take this stress.

24:11.800 --> 24:13.480
That's impossible, sir,

24:13.560 --> 24:16.720
because that Banaspati guy doesn't want
to settle, and I'm sure of that.

24:16.800 --> 24:17.960
[Banaspati] Miss Nayana.

24:20.200 --> 24:22.480
Maybe my hands are outstretched,

24:23.160 --> 24:25.000
but certainly not for begging.

24:25.080 --> 24:29.680
[chuckles] For your sake, I agreed
to settle for 50 grand instead of 500.

24:29.760 --> 24:31.320
You want a settlement?

24:31.400 --> 24:32.280
Wanted,

24:33.120 --> 24:34.560
but not anymore.

24:34.640 --> 24:36.680
Now whatever happens will happen in here.

24:36.760 --> 24:38.560
- And it will sting.
- [Ani clears throat]

24:38.640 --> 24:42.560
[Banaspati] Ah… Come come, Miss Ani.
These guys have started panicking already.

24:42.640 --> 24:45.560
[Nayana] He's bluffing, sir. They had
only one recording device on them,

24:45.640 --> 24:47.440
and it is now safely in Rajesh's custody.

24:48.080 --> 24:49.440
You want me to trust you now?

24:49.520 --> 24:52.960
Sir, as your lawyer I intentionally
withheld the sting information from you

24:53.040 --> 24:54.480
because it does not change anything.

24:54.560 --> 24:57.840
Trust me, sir. Ani's going to admit defeat
on her own today.

25:08.600 --> 25:10.240
[Vishwas] Hey,
I like your shades, man. Nice.

25:11.920 --> 25:12.880
They're bluffing, sir.

25:12.960 --> 25:13.960
[door opens]

25:16.120 --> 25:17.520
[Bhandari] Please sit. You may sit.

25:17.600 --> 25:20.920
- Banaspati versus Fire Clone Deodorant.
- Hey.

25:21.000 --> 25:22.080
She'll do the talking!

25:22.160 --> 25:23.560
Yes, Miss Ananya. Go ahead!

25:24.880 --> 25:26.480
Uh… So Your Honour…

25:26.560 --> 25:27.600
Your Honour,

25:29.480 --> 25:31.560
- I would like to say something!
- What are you doing? Please sit down, sir!

25:31.640 --> 25:32.680
I am handling this.

25:32.760 --> 25:36.000
Mr Banaspati here has placed charges

25:36.080 --> 25:37.640
of corporate fraud against our company,

25:37.720 --> 25:39.320
which we are not in agreement with.

25:39.400 --> 25:42.240
But yes,
we have also been a little careless.

25:43.960 --> 25:45.240
What are you doing, sir?

25:45.320 --> 25:47.840
You are no more our lawyer.

25:50.360 --> 25:53.560
We discovered some lapses
in our manufacturing.

25:53.640 --> 25:55.000
We'll address them immediately.

25:55.080 --> 25:58.280
But all the faulty deodorants found
have been recalled.

25:58.360 --> 26:01.600
And we are willing
to compensate Mr Banaspati.

26:01.680 --> 26:03.320
Compensation amount, Mr Venkat?

26:04.160 --> 26:05.160
Well,

26:05.880 --> 26:07.160
[clears throat]

26:10.600 --> 26:11.640
Uh…

26:11.720 --> 26:14.120
- We agree to their demands!
- You can ask for lot more,

26:14.200 --> 26:15.880
- these guys are loaded!
- [Bhandari] Good! That's settled!

26:15.960 --> 26:18.080
Miss Ananya you have won the case.

26:18.160 --> 26:19.600
- Dismissed!
- [gavel raps]

26:29.480 --> 26:31.760
Ma'am, didn't you tell me
you had deleted that account?

26:31.840 --> 26:33.560
Yeah, yeah. I was about to do it.

26:34.080 --> 26:35.080
Then, uh…

26:37.480 --> 26:39.840
Things got a little more serious
with Mintu.

26:41.880 --> 26:43.120
That means you have feelings for Mintu--

26:43.200 --> 26:44.400
You're asking for a slap.

26:47.440 --> 26:48.440
Yes.

26:48.960 --> 26:51.560
So why didn't you go meet him then? Ma'am!

26:51.640 --> 26:52.800
I did go.

26:53.320 --> 26:55.040
Then I thought, "What do I say?"

26:55.120 --> 26:56.720
This was initially about a name
for the chamber.

26:56.800 --> 26:58.560
But now you and I…

26:59.200 --> 27:00.520
I understand that, ma'am.

27:01.120 --> 27:03.480
But now you've made a mistake.
You might as well own up to him.

27:03.560 --> 27:05.800
[clicks tongue] This partnership's
finally working out.

27:05.880 --> 27:07.840
He'll never be able to trust me again.

27:08.640 --> 27:11.200
If he hates Binu Bindra,
I'm good with that.

27:13.360 --> 27:15.040
But I won't let him hate Sujata.

27:17.040 --> 27:20.000
Why don't you at least tell him that
Binu Bindra won't be coming?

27:20.080 --> 27:21.560
The poor guy's still waiting for you.

27:25.520 --> 27:27.000
[Mintu] Hey, are you on your way?

27:27.080 --> 27:28.560
Are you stuck in traffic?

27:28.640 --> 27:31.720
I'd ordered some coffee for you.
I'm waiting.

27:32.280 --> 27:36.320
Binu, you're coming, right?
Binu, I ordered another coffee for you.

27:36.400 --> 27:40.240
You're coming, right?
Binu, I've been waiting two hours now.

27:41.200 --> 27:42.200
[Munshi] Sujata!

27:43.520 --> 27:44.440
Yes, Mr Munshi?

27:44.520 --> 27:48.040
I have got some designs here
for nameplates.

27:59.280 --> 28:01.320
This is not because
you are like a daughter to me.

28:01.400 --> 28:02.800
You've earned it.

28:04.600 --> 28:05.600
Well done.

28:12.360 --> 28:14.720
Visheshwar,
yes or no is not for me to say.

28:15.440 --> 28:17.280
No one else can decide for you.

28:18.960 --> 28:21.240
This is something you will have
to judge for yourself.

28:22.400 --> 28:23.640
I can't do it, Dad.

28:31.000 --> 28:32.000
Sit, sit.

28:36.320 --> 28:40.080
Look at this. Instead of writing
the victim's name here,

28:40.160 --> 28:41.640
why do they always write state?

28:42.160 --> 28:46.200
Because the crime is committed not just
towards the victim but society also.

28:47.760 --> 28:49.400
That's why the state fights the case.

28:49.480 --> 28:52.400
Have you wondered why in this country,

28:53.880 --> 28:56.080
in every court, every day,

28:57.640 --> 29:00.800
all of society comes to seek justice?

29:02.840 --> 29:03.840
Why?

29:06.800 --> 29:08.600
Because it has full faith that

29:08.680 --> 29:12.200
whatever verdict the judge sitting
on that bench is about to deliver

29:13.320 --> 29:14.640
will be a just verdict.

29:20.000 --> 29:22.160
The judge is also a part of that society.

29:24.080 --> 29:26.200
Who is he to make a decision like this?

29:26.280 --> 29:30.400
It's because that chair
demands that he do it.

29:34.400 --> 29:35.400
Visheshwar,

29:36.160 --> 29:38.520
though you are part of society…

29:40.680 --> 29:42.640
you will have to go beyond it.

29:44.120 --> 29:48.720
So that every decision you make
will be for the benefit of society.

29:48.800 --> 29:53.080
Therefore, before you enter court,
you must leave yourself outside.

29:56.040 --> 29:59.240
All your personal ideals
and principles you hold on to,

30:00.800 --> 30:03.960
all your emotions
have no place on that chair.

30:08.000 --> 30:18.000
ভুয়া লিংক এড়িয়ে চলুন — অফিসিয়াল: -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

30:09.000 --> 30:10.000
So…

30:12.800 --> 30:14.680
you think I'm capable of that, sir?

30:17.360 --> 30:18.360
Son,

30:20.280 --> 30:23.440
for a warrior, the battlefield is
his biggest testing ground.

30:25.240 --> 30:26.600
Out on that field…

30:29.160 --> 30:33.000
the weight of the weapon
will tell you itself

30:34.640 --> 30:37.280
whether you'll be able
to carry it again or not.

31:45.320 --> 31:46.320
This court

31:47.320 --> 31:49.280
pronounces Deepak Ahlawadi

31:49.360 --> 31:52.240
guilty for the murder
of Prateek Meher and Udit Meher…

31:57.000 --> 31:59.040
and awards him the death sentence.

32:05.680 --> 32:06.680
To be hanged…

32:08.840 --> 32:09.840
till death.

34:19.600 --> 34:20.640
Visheshwar.

34:21.520 --> 34:22.800
Dad, uh…

34:27.160 --> 34:28.520
It was very heavy.

34:31.120 --> 34:32.760
Will you be able to carry it again?

34:38.480 --> 34:39.680
Dad, he was…

34:41.960 --> 34:43.920
he was just 24 years old.

34:50.760 --> 34:55.400
He was… He was only 24 years old, Dad.

34:55.480 --> 35:02.160
Only 24 years old, just a boy.

35:07.480 --> 35:09.200
I can't do this.

35:10.280 --> 35:13.480
I'm not fit for that chair, Dad.

35:13.560 --> 35:14.880
I'm not…

35:23.840 --> 35:26.160
[crying]

35:53.960 --> 35:54.960
[Sujata] Mintu.

36:05.000 --> 36:07.600
Don't you want to check
whose chamber it is before you enter?

36:26.400 --> 36:27.280
[Mintu] Mr Munshi,

36:28.720 --> 36:29.640
mine.

36:35.680 --> 36:36.840
Order, my friend.

36:37.880 --> 36:38.880
Take a pic, man.

36:38.960 --> 36:41.360
- Ma'am, you join him too.
- Hey. No, no.

36:41.440 --> 36:43.160
- Come join me, Sujata.
- No, no. It's okay.

36:43.240 --> 36:45.240
- Come on. Come.
- Join him, ma'am. Join him.

36:45.320 --> 36:46.360
[Munshi] Go on.

36:46.440 --> 36:47.440
Ready?

36:49.440 --> 36:50.440
[shutter clicks]

36:55.200 --> 36:58.400
Sujata, Ani just won her first case!

36:58.480 --> 36:59.480
[Sujata] Wow, Ani!

37:00.400 --> 37:03.040
[no audible dialogue]

37:10.880 --> 37:13.400
DISTRICT COURT,
PATPARGANJ, DELHI

37:14.640 --> 37:15.760
[phone chimes, buzzes]

37:18.880 --> 37:19.880
\PLEASE SEND $2100.

37:19.960 --> 37:21.880
\[Banaspati] Ivanka. My bride to be!

37:21.960 --> 37:23.440
Hmm…

37:23.520 --> 37:25.360
She's even learning Hindi for me.

37:25.440 --> 37:26.600
[laughing]

37:26.680 --> 37:29.680
Send 2,100 please.

37:29.760 --> 37:32.520
- She's got you by your armpits, buddy.
- [clicks tongue]

37:34.080 --> 37:37.160
Why should only Binu like the dessert?
I could like it too, couldn't I?

37:38.200 --> 37:39.280
[chuckles]

37:45.120 --> 37:46.320
[Mintu] You really like it?

37:50.480 --> 37:51.480
Your Honour?

38:35.120 --> 38:38.400
Could you guys make some room
on this nameplate for one more name?

38:38.480 --> 38:39.880
Balli, Negi…

38:42.760 --> 38:43.960
Tyagi and associates.

38:44.040 --> 38:45.320
Tyagi, you quit the judges chair?

38:45.400 --> 38:47.560
[Banaspati] Wow.
Milord's become a lawyer again.
